caption.p: Chemical character of essential oils from maaliol producing species, and P. incisa from Blue Mountains. Yield is in % g/g fresh leaf weight, AI is arithmetic index and Pub. AI is the published reference value of arithmetic index. SUS = P. suborbicularis, STA = P. striatiflora, MNF = P. sp. Minyon Falls, OSF = P. sp. Olney State Forest, CAA = P. caerulea, BGB = P. sp. Baking Board, TOR = P. sp. Thredbo River, GRR, P. sp. Gibraltar Range, ASS = P. aspalathoides, PIA = P. sp. Piliga.

fn.p: * Yield is in % g/g fresh leaf weight. ** RI-a is the calculated retention index and RI-b is the published reference value of the retention index.
